  "base_commit": "92ee2b8fbc69353993e59a0227a11a5761de4406",
  "pr_number": 4255,
  "issue_number": 4094,
  "issue_title": "v4: `.meta()` behaviour questions/bugs",
  "issue_body": "```ts\nconst jobId = z\n  .string()\n  .refine(() => {\n    // complex validation logic\n    return true;\n  })\n  .meta({ id: \"jobId\" });\n\nconsole.log(\n  JSON.stringify(\n    z.toJSONSchema(\n      z.object({\n        current: jobId,\n        previous: jobId.describe(\"previous job id\"),\n      }),\n      {\n        reused: \"ref\",\n      }\n    ),\n    null,\n    2\n  )\n);\n```\n\nThis currently throws an error:\n\n```bash\n/Users/samc/work/zod-openapi-2/node_modules/.pnpm/@zod+core@0.3.3/node_modules/@zod/core/dist/commonjs/registries.js:18\n                throw new Error(`ID ${meta.id} already exists in the registry`);\n                      ^\n\nError: ID jobId already exists in the registry\n```\n\nWhich I don't believe is the most intuitive behaviour?\n\nThe alternative would be\n\n```ts\nconsole.log(\n  JSON.stringify(\n    z.toJSONSchema(\n      z.object({\n        current: baseJobId,\n        previous: baseJobId.meta({ description: \"previous job id\" }),\n      }),\n      {\n        reused: \"ref\",\n      }\n    ),\n    null,\n    2\n  )\n);\n```\n\nwhich generates:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"current\": {\n      \"id\": \"jobId\",\n      \"type\": \"string\"\n    },\n    \"previous\": {\n      \"description\": \"previous job id\",\n      \"type\": \"string\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"required\": [\n    \"current\",\n    \"previous\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nWhich isn't too bad but the ideal behaviour would I think be:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"current\": {\n      \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/jobId\"\n    },\n    \"previous\": {\n      \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/jobId\"\n      \"description\": \"previous job id\",\n    }\n  },\n  \"required\": [\n    \"current\",\n    \"previous\"\n  ],\n  \"$defs\": {\n    \"jobId\": {\n      \"id\": \"jobId\",\n      \"type\": \"string\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nHowever, this might require a change to how `.meta()` works. Ideally every call would have to create a new instance rather than overwriting the previous version in the store.\n\nWIth `zod-openapi` I made the decision to create new instances with every successive `.meta()/.openapi()` metadata but also merged previous data but discarded the `id` property after I received some requests/bug reports. This produced some pretty awesome reusable schema: https://github.com/samchungy/zod-openapi/releases/tag/v4.0.0",
  "merged_at": "2025-04-21T22:52:41Z",
